  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "This is the vision that the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        revealed to Obadiah concerning the land of Edom.We have heard a message from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tthat an ambassador was sent to the nations
        to say,\n\t\u201CGet ready, everyone!\n\tLet\u2019s assemble our armies and
        attack Edom!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Edom\u2019s Judgment Announced"
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Edom,\n\t\u201CI will cut
        you down to size among the nations;\n\tyou will be greatly despised.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have been deceived by your own pride\n\tbecause you live in a
        rock fortress\n\tand make your home high in the mountains.\n\t\u2018Who can
        ever reach us way up here?\u2019\n\tyou ask boastfully.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But even if you soar as high as eagles\n\tand build your nest among
        the stars,\n\tI will bring you crashing down,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf thieves came at night and robbed you\n\t(what a disaster
        awaits you!),\n\tthey would not take everything.\n\tThose who harvest grapes\n\talways
        leave a few for the poor.\n\tBut your enemies will wipe you out completely!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Every nook and cranny of Edom[COMMENT[0]]will be searched and looted.\n\tEvery
        treasure will be found and taken.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Esau; '
        - ft: also in 8b, 9, 18, 19, 21.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll your allies will turn against you.\n\tThey will help to
        chase you from your land.\n\tThey will promise you peace\n\twhile plotting
        to deceive and destroy you.\n\tYour trusted friends will set traps for you,\n\tand
        you won\u2019t even know about it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time not a single wise person\n\twill be left in the whole
        land of Edom,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor
        on the mountains of Edom\n\tI will destroy everyone who has understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The mightiest warriors of Teman\n\twill be terrified,\n\tand everyone
        on the mountains of Edom\n\twill be cut down in the slaughter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Reasons for Edom\u2019s Punishment"
      content: "\u201CBecause of the violence you did\n\tto your close relatives
        in Israel,[COMMENT[0]]you will be filled with shame\n\tand destroyed forever.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'your brother Jacob. '
        - ft: "The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged
            throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes to the individual patriarch
            and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "When they were invaded,\n\tyou stood aloof, refusing to help them.\n\tForeign
        invaders carried off their wealth\n\tand cast lots to divide up Jerusalem,\n\tbut
        you acted like one of Israel\u2019s enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou should not have gloated\n\twhen they exiled your relatives
        to distant lands.\n\tYou should not have rejoiced\n\twhen the people of Judah
        suffered such misfortune.\n\tYou should not have spoken arrogantly\n\tin
        that terrible time of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You should not have plundered the land of Israel\n\twhen they were
        suffering such calamity.\n\tYou should not have gloated over their destruction\n\twhen
        they were suffering such calamity.\n\tYou should not have seized their wealth\n\twhen
        they were suffering such calamity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You should not have stood at the crossroads,\n\tkilling those who
        tried to escape.\n\tYou should not have captured the survivors\n\tand handed
        them over in their terrible time of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Edom Destroyed, Israel Restored
      content: "\u201CThe day is near when I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\twill
        judge all godless nations!\n\tAs you have done to Israel,\n\tso it will be
        done to you.\n\tAll your evil deeds\n\twill fall back on your own heads.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just as you swallowed up my people\n\ton my holy mountain,\n\tso
        you and the surrounding nations\n\twill swallow the punishment I pour out
        on you.\n\tYes, all you nations will drink and stagger\n\tand disappear from
        history.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]] will become a refuge for those who
        escape;\n\tit will be a holy place.\n\tAnd the people of Israel[COMMENT[1]]
        will come back\n\tto reclaim their inheritance.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Mount Zion.
      - number: '1:17b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'house of Jacob; '
        - ft: also in 18. See note on 10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel will be a raging fire,\n\tand Edom a field of
        dry stubble.\n\tThe descendants of Joseph will be a flame\n\troaring across
        the field, devouring everything.\n\tThere will be no survivors in Edom.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen my people living in the Negev\n\twill occupy the mountains
        of Edom.\n\tThose living in the foothills of Judah[COMMENT[0]]will possess
        the Philistine plains\n\tand take over the fields of Ephraim and Samaria.\n\tAnd
        the people of Benjamin\n\twill occupy the land of Gilead.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Shephelah.
    - title: 
      content: "The exiles of Israel will return to their land\n\tand occupy the
        Phoenician coast as far north as Zarephath.\n\tThe captives from Jerusalem
        exiled in the north[COMMENT[0]]will return home and resettle the towns of
        the Negev.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Sepharad.
    - title: 
      content: "Those who have been rescued[COMMENT[0]] will go up to[COMMENT[1]]
        Mount Zion in Jerusalem\n\tto rule over the mountains of Edom.\n\tAnd the
        <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>\n\thimself will be king!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '1:21a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: Rescuers.
      - number: '1:21b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: from.
